-> Variables are containers for storing data values, like numbers and characters.
-> A variable in C is a memory location associated with some name in order to store some form of data and retrieve it when required.
-> In C, all variables must be declared before they are used, usually at the beginning of the function before any executable statements.
-> A declaration announces the properties of variables it has type name and list of variables.
-> An initialization assigns the value to the variable

---How to declare a variable
data_type variable_name;

---How to initialize a variable
variable_name = value based on the type of the variable;

We can also initialize a variable while declaring it
data_type variable_name = value based on the type of the variable;
